Amid the rising debate over Google's potential breakup in 2025, one thing has become evident: your marketing strategies for a plumbing business don't need to be radically changed. There may be some instability, but in the end, it all comes down to winning customer trust through long-term relationship building. You may have to adopt a mix of innovative SEO techniques to make a difference. In fact, it applies to other local businesses as well. Here are some insights regarding this.

* **Podcasting**

Nowadays, access to local newspapers has decreased significantly in the U.S. Many counties no longer receive their local news. Due to this, a large number of Americans remain devoid of essential updates. Some sources forecast a rise in demand for podcasting due to this. Data suggest that there will be about 110 million podcast audience in the U.S. alone by 2029, representing nearly â…“ of its existing population. What does it mean for your plumbing business? You should hire a reliable [plumber marketing agency](https://reverbico.com/blog/marketing-for-plumbing-businesses/) that can efficiently ride these waves and get you noticed. If you've lost your reach and voice in the region due to diminishing access to local newspapers, a marketing agency can help revive it through podcasting. Podcasts help build a close-knit community, which can become a powerful driver for your business.

* **Diversifying the style of social communications**

2024 was once all about Reddit. Google searchers flocked to this platform to have authentic conversations with real humans because it created a natural trust factor for them. How can your plumbing business benefit from this trend? A marketing agency can show you the path. They can help your brand or business join a platform where customer relationships are easy to nurture. The focus should be on authenticity. Some communities or platforms encourage anonymity, which may not benefit a local business like yours, where real connections are key. So, what's the solution? A [marketing agency](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Econversions) you can trust will find new ways to integrate your brand into the community's daily activities.

* **Reimagining customer service**

In the 20th century, local businesses often had a help desk on their property where customers could call and discuss their concerns. No matter the era, customer service is going to be the central focus. Studies suggest that up to 92% of customers prefer receiving an owner's reply to their reviews, especially since most people spend a significant part of their day online. For 21st-century local businesses, this indicates that your customer service efforts should also shift to online platforms. Hence, you should hire an agency that will make your agency visible across different channels. They should list your business correctly and help you earn high-quality reviews and ratings. 

At the core of all marketing initiatives should be a focus on driving customer satisfaction. It becomes easier to manage this aspect when your business highlights key factors such as proximity, expertise, friendly service, and a comprehensive range of services. An expert agency can optimize for 'near me' searches and create targeted content around the services you offer, helping customers make faster, more informed decisions. When things are just a click away, they feel more confident hiring you for their needs.
